  "prompt": "How do I raise berries in Pokemon Sun / Moon?",
  "response": "In Pok\u00e9mon Sun and Moon, you can grow berries by following these steps:\n\n1. Obtain Berries: Get berry seeds from NPCs, find them on the ground, or receive them as rewards.\n\n2. Unlock the Berry Field: Progress in the game until you reach Poke Pelago, which is unlocked after receiving the Ride Pager.\n\n3. Use Isle Aplenny: This is the berry-growing area in Poke Pelago.\n\n4. Plant Berries: \n- Select Isle Aplenny\n- Choose which berries to plant\n- Each plot can grow multiple berries\n\n5. Waiting and Harvesting:\n- Berries take time to grow\n- You can speed up growth by developing the island\n- Berries will be ready to harvest when they're fully grown\n\n6. Optional Tips:\n- Upgrade Isle Aplenny to get more plots and faster growth\n- Some berries take longer to grow than others\n- You can plant multiple types of berries simultaneously\n\nRemember that Poke Pelago is accessible from the bottom screen menu, and you don't need to be physically present to grow berries - they'll continue growing even when you're not actively playing.",
